# what-files-in-src-directory
author: tlawson

levels:

  - beginner

  - basic

type: normal

category: must-know

links:

  - '[What is the difference in Android test and Test ](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/34397524/whats-the-difference-between-src-androidtest-and-src-test-folders)'

---
## Content

When you select the Project View, you will see the src directory. The `src`directory contains all code and resource files in the following subdirectories:

* `androidTest`contains code for instrumentation tests that run on an Android device.
```
package com.example.tammy.helloworld;

import android.content.Context;
import android.support.test.InstrumentationRegistry;
import android.support.test.runner.AndroidJUnit4;

import org.junit.Test;
import org.junit.runner.RunWith;

import static org.junit.Assert.*;

/**
 * Instrumented test, which will execute on an Android device.
 *
 * @see <a href="http://d.android.com/tools/testing">Testing documentation</a>
 */
@RunWith(AndroidJUnit4.class)
public class ExampleInstrumentedTest {
    @Test
    public void useAppContext() throws Exception {
        // Context of the app under test.
        Context appContext = InstrumentationRegistry.getTargetContext();

        assertEquals("com.example.tammy.helloworld", appContext.getPackageName());
    }
}
```

* `main`contains the "main" source files: the Android code and resources shared by all build variants.
* `java` contains Java code sources.
* `res`contains application resources, such as drawable files, layout files, and User Interface string. 
* `test`contains code for local tests that run on your host Java Virtual Machine.

```
package com.example.tammy.helloworld;

import org.junit.Test;

import static org.junit.Assert.*;

/**
 * Example local unit test, which will execute on the development machine (host).
 *
 * @see <a href="http://d.android.com/tools/testing">Testing documentation</a>
 */
public class ExampleUnitTest {
    @Test
    public void addition_isCorrect() throws Exception {
        assertEquals(4, 2 + 2);
    }
}
```


---
## Practice

What is the purpose of AndroidTest?
???

* Used for Instrumentation unit test that run on an Android device. 
* Contains source files.
* Run locally on the Java Virtual Machine for local test

---
## Revision

What is the purpose of the src folder?
???

* Contains all codes such as application code and reource files.
* Used to capture all Java code and Gradle builds.
* Contains codes for the project. 
